{
  "texts": [
    "Bartram (2006) claimed that parental impact included role modelling positive/negative behaviours, communicating educational regrets, and helping children comprehend linguistic relevance and position.",
    "Larsen and Long (1991) believed that parents affected their children's language and culture preferences.",
    "This attitude and behaviour shaped their perspectives and affected their language learning and proficiency positively or negatively.",
    "Wilkins (1974) stated the same when he said that children's attitudes primarily reflected upon parents' attitudes.",
    "Thus, it could be inferred that parents' attitudes determined both the success of language learning and failure."
  ]
}